  "response_text": "The commercial opens on a large Popeyes chicken sandwich centered against a vivid orange background. The sandwich sits on printed Popeyes paper. A glossy, golden-brown top bun rests over a thick, craggy piece of fried chicken whose crunchy coating protrudes beyond the bun on both sides. Under the chicken, pale sauce and green pickle slices are visible above the bottom bun. Crumbs are scattered around the base, emphasizing the rough, crisp texture of the breading.\n\nThe orange fills the screen briefly, then the setting changes to a Popeyes restaurant kitchen. Stainless-steel appliances, counters, white ceiling lights, and orange Popeyes packaging create a busy back-of-house environment. A Black adult male employee with a short gray beard wears an orange Popeyes shirt, a black apron, a gray cap, and white gloves. He lifts and handles a large tan paper bag printed with the Popeyes logo, holding it up in front of him. The bag appears to be an ingredient sack.\n\nThe employee moves energetically beside a white plastic tub and stainless equipment. His body leans and twists as if working with rhythm, one arm raised while the other holds a shiny metal container or shaker. A close view shows his gloved hand gripping the silver cylinder near the side of a metal appliance. The action visually connects the kitchen work with care and enthusiasm. Nearby, another Popeyes worker in the same orange shirt, black apron, and gloves appears at the edge of the counter, watching or assisting.\n\nA round wire basket filled with chicken pieces coated in orange batter is shown over a tub. The basket is lifted, and thick orange marinade drips down through the wire into the container below. A whisk or utensil rests in another tub of orange liquid in the foreground. The main employee holds the basket over a white bin, letting excess batter drain. He appears focused, with a small smile as he works. The second employee remains to the right, partly visible, standing close to the prep station.\n\nThe main employee then presses both gloved hands into a large white bin of flour or breading mixture. He leans over the tub, mixing and coating the pieces with firm, repeated motions. His expression looks cheerful and engaged. Flour gathers around his hands as he works the chicken through the dry coating. The stainless kitchen remains visible behind him, with stacked tan ingredient bags on the left and metal ovens or cabinets in the background.\n\nThe sandwich returns in close detail. The fried chicken’s rough, golden crust fills the view, with glossy pickle slices and a line of pale sauce below it. Tiny white disclaimer text appears along the bottom edge but is too small to read clearly. The view widens to show the sandwich on Popeyes-branded paper with fries arranged to the right. The bun is shiny and rounded, the chicken layer is thick and uneven, and the pickles form a green band under the crunchy filet. In the background, the restaurant kitchen is softly visible, including white tile and blurred orange packaging.\n\nWhite promotional text appears above the sandwich, reading “$4.99 Chicken Sandwich,” while the sandwich and fries remain centered on the counter. The fine print continues along the bottom in very small white text. The final images return to the kitchen from a wider view. A large white “Popeyes” logo appears across the center, then expands to “Popeyes Louisiana Kitchen.” Behind the logo, the same employee in orange and black moves along the stainless prep line. On the left, a tray piled with fried chicken pieces sits on the counter. The employee’s back shows white writing on the orange shirt, including the phrase “love that chicken,” as the commercial ends with the brand logo over the busy Popeyes kitchen.",
